(1940)

25
00:04:45,237 --> 00:04:46,477
It's just a rumor.

26
00:04:46,683 --> 00:04:48,103
Ghosts don't exist!

27
00:04:48,636 --> 00:04:49,943
It's not a rumor, Mr. Sing.

28
00:04:50,136 --> 00:04:52,520
The guy who survived has gone mad.

29
00:04:52,743 --> 00:04:55,000
He's been telling everyone
in the market.

30
00:04:55,176 --> 00:04:56,716
- It's true.
- How about this?

31
00:04:57,103 --> 00:04:58,783
I'll double your fee.

32
00:04:58,850 --> 00:05:00,076
Demolish it or burn it down.

33
00:05:00,087 --> 00:05:01,843
Just make sure
the Dark Shadow House is gone.

34
00:05:01,950 --> 00:05:05,623
Even for ten or twenty times
more money, we won't do it.

35
00:05:05,963 --> 00:05:08,370
We'd rather keep our lives
to be with our families.

36
00:05:09,056 --> 00:05:10,437
Here's your deposit.

37
00:05:11,300 --> 00:05:13,340
- You idiots are just...
- Goodbye.

38
00:05:13,446 --> 00:05:14,446
Go, go.

39
00:05:14,760 --> 00:05:17,093
What the hell? They're all useless.

40
00:05:17,526 --> 00:05:19,400
It's the same every damn time!

41
00:05:20,940 --> 00:05:21,940
I've paid them.

42
00:05:22,280 --> 00:05:23,720
I've threatened them.

43
00:05:23,846 --> 00:05:25,360
No one has come through.

44
00:05:25,666 --> 00:05:26,666
It's the ghost of…

45
00:05:28,660 --> 00:05:31,513
The ghost is so vengeful.
So who would dare demolish it?

46
00:05:32,313 --> 00:05:34,853
Sing, we're already rich.

47
00:05:35,113 --> 00:05:37,960
We have more money than
we'll ever need in this life.

48
00:05:38,146 --> 00:05:40,326
Not to mention
our assets and farms.

49
00:05:40,606 --> 00:05:42,466
Why do you need that piece of land?

50
00:05:44,040 --> 00:05:45,400
Have you any idea

51
00:05:46,213 --> 00:05:47,600
how much those foreigners

52
00:05:48,153 --> 00:05:49,353
offered me?

53
00:05:50,113 --> 00:05:52,746
More than decades of running the
rice mills would ever make me.

54
00:05:53,033 --> 00:05:55,000
Not selling it right now
would be stupid.

55
00:05:57,999 --> 00:06:00,240
You're gonna keep
that house to shame yourself?

56
00:06:00,593 --> 00:06:03,240
Has there ever been
a night you sleep soundly?

57
00:06:05,973 --> 00:06:07,366
Let's demolish it

58
00:06:08,519 --> 00:06:10,320
for our peace of mind

59
00:06:11,433 --> 00:06:12,793
and our son.

60
00:06:14,553 --> 00:06:15,553
Of course.

61
00:06:16,526 --> 00:06:18,400
But no one would accept the job.

62
00:06:18,659 --> 00:06:20,072
Who's gonna demolish it for us?

63
00:06:20,686 --> 00:06:23,640
The problem is not
who's gonna demolish it.

64
00:06:27,199 --> 00:06:28,199
The problem…

65
00:06:29,526 --> 00:06:31,599
is the ghost haunting that house.

66
00:06:36,166 --> 00:06:51,600
(Buddhist chant)

67
00:06:56,157 --> 00:06:58,597
You finally showed up,
you malicious ghost.

68
00:06:59,403 --> 00:07:01,216
Please forgive me.

69
00:07:02,057 --> 00:07:03,800
This must be done.

70
00:07:04,230 --> 00:07:06,257
Please leave
and be reborn, Ms. Malai.

71
00:07:06,643 --> 00:07:09,543
You died, Ms. Malai.
Why do you care about this place?

72
00:07:09,650 --> 00:07:11,120
Give it to me, please.

73
00:07:20,409 --> 00:07:21,840
I thought you'd be better.

74
00:07:59,537 --> 00:08:00,537
Open!

75
00:08:00,543 --> 00:08:02,143
Hey, what the hell?!

76
00:08:04,943 --> 00:08:06,223
Ms. Malai,

77
00:08:06,730 --> 00:08:08,480
don't hurt me, please.

78
00:08:09,237 --> 00:08:11,997
Forgive me.
I won't step in here again.

79
00:08:12,003 --> 00:08:13,003
Hey!

80
00:08:13,310 --> 00:08:14,630
Why are you begging?

81
00:08:15,103 --> 00:08:16,320
Stop being scared!

82
00:08:17,183 --> 00:08:18,760
Come out if you dare!

83
00:08:19,530 --> 00:08:21,117
- Come out!
- Sing!

84
