204
00:18:37,850 --> 00:18:39,400
Come in, Mai.

205
00:18:40,510 --> 00:18:42,510
I've been waiting for you.

206
00:18:43,897 --> 00:18:45,000
Who are you?

207
00:18:46,326 --> 00:18:47,600
How did you know me?

208
00:19:51,080 --> 00:19:52,240
I'm sorry.

209
00:19:53,437 --> 00:19:54,924
May I call you "sister"?

210
00:19:55,917 --> 00:19:57,800
How did you know me, sister?

211
00:19:59,090 --> 00:20:00,770
Maybe you knew my parents.

212
00:20:16,063 --> 00:20:17,323
This is for you.

213
00:22:35,350 --> 00:22:36,350
No boat.

214
00:24:04,337 --> 00:24:07,680
I'll take you back
to witness the entire story.

215
00:24:08,850 --> 00:24:09,850
Follow me.

216
00:24:47,383 --> 00:24:55,053
(1920)

217
00:26:11,770 --> 00:26:13,283
- Thanks.
- Thank you, ma'am.

218
00:27:40,837 --> 00:27:41,837
Ow!

219
00:27:52,063 --> 00:27:54,040
And this is Ms. Malai,

220
00:27:54,303 --> 00:27:55,543
my bride-to-be.

221
00:27:59,927 --> 00:28:04,460
(House of the Dark Shadows
novel: Phakhinai, screenplay: Wannason)

222
00:28:04,860 --> 00:28:09,393
(House of the Dark Shadows
novel: Phakhinai, screenplay: Wannason)

223
00:28:11,270 --> 00:28:12,270
Ow!

224
00:28:33,970 --> 00:28:34,970
Miss!

225
00:28:36,370 --> 00:28:37,370
Miss!

226
00:28:37,656 --> 00:28:38,656
Miss,

227
00:28:39,076 --> 00:28:41,200
what are you trying to do, huh?

228
00:28:42,239 --> 00:28:45,499
- Miss? Miss? Miss!
- No, I want to die!

229
00:28:45,766 --> 00:28:47,200
I want to die!

230
00:28:48,306 --> 00:28:49,306
Miss?

231
00:28:53,199 --> 00:28:54,632
Please sit down, Miss.

232
00:28:56,806 --> 00:28:59,120
If you won't, I'll sit far away.

233
00:29:00,426 --> 00:29:01,426
That's okay.

234
00:29:02,306 --> 00:29:03,520
Don't mind me.

235
00:29:04,899 --> 00:29:05,899
Please sit.

236
00:29:25,450 --> 00:29:28,720
Our suffering is like
rivers and rain, Miss.

237
00:29:29,403 --> 00:29:31,200
It comes and goes.

238
00:29:32,777 --> 00:29:35,120
No matter what
caused your suffering,

239
00:29:37,000 --> 00:29:39,800
I believe it shall pass soon.

240
00:29:53,759 --> 00:29:54,880
- You!
- You!

241
00:30:07,497 --> 00:30:08,497
Uh…

242
00:30:09,803 --> 00:30:10,843
Are you hurt?

243
00:30:11,570 --> 00:30:12,570
No.

244
00:30:18,843 --> 00:30:19,843
I'm sorry.

245
00:30:20,269 --> 00:30:22,320
I didn't mean to offend you.

246
00:30:22,383 --> 00:30:25,096
I just noticed the red cotton
flower stamens in your hair.

247
00:30:31,110 --> 00:30:32,110
Excuse me.

248
00:30:55,377 --> 00:30:57,200
You're helping me
carry my suitcase.

249
00:30:57,856 --> 00:31:00,150
I don't know your name.

250
00:31:00,977 --> 00:31:02,164
I'm Malai.

251
00:31:02,880 --> 00:31:03,880
I'm Dech.

252
00:31:05,997 --> 00:31:06,997
Oh.

253
00:31:10,903 --> 00:31:12,200
Uh, there's…

254
00:31:12,530 --> 00:31:14,880
a red cotton flower stamen on you.

255
00:31:15,950 --> 00:31:17,320
Don't worry about it, Malai.

256
00:31:17,937 --> 00:31:20,850
Your handkerchief is clean.
Don't dirty it on my account.

257
00:31:21,483 --> 00:31:25,000
Please take it.
As my thanks for helping me.

258
00:31:39,010 --> 00:31:40,360
You've arrived, Malai.

259
00:31:51,743 --> 00:31:53,720
I'm on my way to wait at the pier.

260
00:31:57,477 --> 00:31:59,584
I arrived just now, Your Lordship.

261
00:32:00,183 --> 00:32:03,763
I ran into Dech
in the red cotton garden.

262
00:32:03,917 --> 00:32:06,677
So he offered to carry my suitcase
and show me the way.

263
00:32:06,870 --> 00:32:08,120
I'm glad you two met.

264
00:32:09,123 --> 00:32:12,800
That's Dech, my valet and confidant.

265
00:32:13,343 --> 00:32:15,360
He's the one
I trust most in this house.

266
00:32:15,870 --> 00:32:18,080
Thank you for trusting me, my lord.

267
00:32:19,523 --> 00:32:20,789
And this is…

268
00:32:21,763 --> 00:32:22,903
Ms. Malai,

269
00:32:23,837 --> 00:32:25,240
my bride-to-be.

270
00:32:36,150 --> 00:32:37,683
You must be tired from the journey.

271
00:32:38,157 --> 00:32:39,560
Come in the house and rest,

272
00:32:40,050 --> 00:32:42,117
